  "title": "Decorative LGBT+ Wall Flags",
  "description": "Adds decorative LGBT+ wall flags! Used only as decoration",
  "body": "<p><img src=\"https://i.imgur.com/CeN8h9G.png\" width=\"766\" height=\"170\" /></p>\n<p><strong><br />Have any suggestion? Want to report a bug? We have a Discord server! You can join and ask anything you want!</strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://discord.gg/U7ue38S2QX\"><img src=\"https://discord.com/api/guilds/922100907360018432/widget.png?style=banner2\" /></a><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><br /></span></p>\n<h2>Introduction</h2>\n<p>This is a mod that aims to add decorative wall flags themed after the LGBT+ flags! This is a mod about expression and decoration. There are no extra mechanics, no new biomes, no new mobs, all this mod adds is just decorative LGBT+ flags and nothing else.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>For obtaining these flags, you have to craft a blank wall flag first, and then use different patterns of colored dyes in order to craft the flag you want!</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>I highly recommend using <a href=\"https://www.curseforge.com/minecraft/mc-mods/jei/files/4494410\"><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Just Enough Items</span></a> for checking the crafting recipes this mod has.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>This mod is for Forge and there will never be a Fabric port.</strong></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Screenshots</h2>\n<div class=\"spoiler\">\n<p><img src=\"https://i.imgur.com/AeLKKd9.png\" width=\"681\" height=\"327\" /></p>\n</div>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<div id=\"s3gt_translate_tooltip_mini\" class=\"s3gt_translate_tooltip_mini_box\" style=\"background: initial !important; border: initial !important; border-radius: initial !important; border-spacing: initial !important; border-collapse: initial !important; direction: ltr !important; flex-direction: initial !important; font-weight: initial !important; height: initial !important; letter-spacing: initial !important; min-width: initial !important; max-width: initial !important; min-height: initial !important; max-height: in